# TheLawyer — Foundations API request catalog.
#
# One request per endpoint, checked into the repo, so the API can be exercised
# deterministically and reviewably (complements the OpenAPI/Scalar surface).
#
# HOST + secrets come from http/.env (dotenv) — NEVER inline them here:
#   - Aspire assigns the API a dynamic port each run. `scripts/run-and-wait.ps1`
#     boots the stack and writes API_BASE into http/.env automatically.
#   - http/.env is gitignored; http/.env.example is the committed template.
#
# Usage (VS Code REST Client / Rider / Visual Studio .http runner):
#   1. pwsh scripts/run-and-wait.ps1
#   2. open this file, click "Send Request" above any block.

@host = {{$dotenv API_BASE}}
@token = {{$dotenv TOKEN}}

### Liveness probe — process is up (no auth)
GET {{host}}/alive

### Readiness / health check (no auth)
GET {{host}}/health

### Ping — confirms the request pipeline end-to-end (anonymous in Foundations)
GET {{host}}/api/v1/ping
Accept: application/json

### OpenAPI document (Development only)
GET {{host}}/openapi/v1.json
Accept: application/json

###
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Template for the authed, tenant-scoped, idempotent endpoints that land with
# later epics. Kept here so every future request honours the cross-cutting
# contract: a test OIDC bearer token, the tenant header, and an idempotency key.
# The token is a TEST identity from http/.env — never a real one.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# ### Create matter (authed, tenant-scoped, idempotent) — EXAMPLE, not yet implemented
# POST {{host}}/api/v1/matters
# Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
# X-Tenant-Id: {{$dotenv TENANT_ID}}
# Idempotency-Key: {{$guid}}
# Content-Type: application/json
#
# {
#   "title": "Sample matter",
#   "clientId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"
# }
